article.headline: UCF 66, Rhode Island 54
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (STATS) -- UCF used a big second-half performance to beat Rhode Island 66-54 on Monday night and advance to the semifinals of the College Basketball Invitational. The Knights (21-11) trailed 30-27 at halftime, shooting 30.8 percent as leading scorer Marcus Jordan was held to two points on 1-of-9 shooting -- 0 for 5 from 3-point range. Jordan never found his stroke, finishing 2 of 11 from the field for a season-low four points, but it didn't hurt his team. UCF opened the second half on an 18-5 run, hitting eight of its first 11 shots to take a 10-point lead. The Knights shot 17 for 25 (68.0 percent) after halftime, holding the Rams (20-14) to 39.1 percent shooting. The Rams got off to a good start, with leading scorer Delroy James scoring nine of their first 13 points. The senior forward, though, had just one more point before halftime and finished with 18 as the only Rhode Island player in double figures. Sophomore forward Keith Clanton led UCF with 16 points and nine rebounds. Rhode Island shot 44.0 percent and went 5 for 12 from beyond the arc in the first half.
